        <h1>LeetCode 3370: Smallest Number With All Set Bits (C++)</h1>

        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given a positive integer n. Your task is to find the smallest number x such that: x is greater than or equal to n, and the binary representation of x consists only of set bits (1s).
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: n = 5<br>
                Output: 7<br>
                Explanation: The binary representation of 7 is 111, which is the smallest number greater than or equal to 5 with all bits set.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int smallestNumber(int n) {
        // Start with x = 1 (binary: 1)
        // Keep doubling x (shifting left) until x - 1 &gt;= n
        // x - 1 gives us a number with all bits set
        // For example: x = 8 (1000), x - 1 = 7 (0111)
        
        int x = 1;
        while (x - 1 &lt; n) {
            x &lt;&lt;= 1; // Left shift (multiply by 2)
        }
        
        return x - 1;
    }
};</code></pre>
